The paper deals with the problem of constructing dominating sets in wireless networks, which is a fundamental problem in the field of network algorithms and optimization. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also presents randomized and polynomial-time algorithms, which suggests that it could belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also deals with communication topologies and graph modeling, which could place it in cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
